cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is about the robustness of neural networks trained via gradient descent with early stopping to label noise. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary category of the paper. The paper also discusses the empirical robustness of deep networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses image classification experiments to demonstrate its results, which could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the capacity of overparameterized neural networks, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses mathematical proofs to support its claims, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
